\gamma$: penalty weight based on product sensitivity

For the purpose of establishing a tractable optimization framework, several simplifying assumptions were adopted in the thermal-energy model. First, the cooling efficiency (
η c
) of the refrigeration unit was assumed constant throughout the delivery route. In practice, this efficiency fluctuates with compressor load, ambient temperature, and vehicle speed. The constant assumption allows the model to capture the overall energy trend without requiring continuous thermodynamic recalibration, though it may lead to a minor approximation error (estimated within 3–7% under normal temperature variation).
